      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW DANGER (1) jumped well from this draw last time and was prominent throughout before holding third (22.66) in a Maiden at Geelong over 400m. Looks the one to beat on best. WILD LARRY (4) was unwanted in betting last start but proved too quick with an all-the-way win over 390m at this track in a Bottom Up - Maiden, scoring by 0.6 lengths (22.72). One of the prime contenders. PAW GEORGIE (3) steps out at this track for the first time after an average run at the latest appearance, finishing fourth at Ballarat over 390m behind Mrs. Winston (23.00). The form from her last run stacks up well. Likely to be about the money. PARIS MASH (2) is a Jordan Formosa-trained newcomer by Barcia Bale out of Levitation. Drawn well and should get her chance. Can sneak into the frame with the right run.",
